						               													<description>The Designer Website:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Byzantium is a card game for 1, 2, 3, or 4 players. It can thus play as a form of solitaire, or as a competitive game, depending upon how many wish to be involved. Players take turns in placing cards on the table forming an elaborate hierarchy that must obey a few strict rules. The aim is to place all of your cards, while preventing your opponents from doing so.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Use two suits from a deck of playing cards, one red, one black. Place an Ace in the centre of the table, and place the other Ace crossed over it. Shuffle the other 24 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Connecting Cards:&amp;#10;The main gameplay consists of connecting cards to form hierarchies. To connect a card in your hand to one in the tableau, the following conditions must be met:&amp;#10;1. It must not overlap any of the cards in the tableau.&amp;#10;2. It must not touch any card other than the one it is connecting to.&amp;#10;3. Its short side must be placed flush against a side of the card in the tableau.&amp;#10;4. The touching sides must touch in their centres.&amp;#10;5. The two cards must be of the same colour.&amp;#10;6. It must be at most three cards distant from the Aces. (It must connect to the Aces, or connect to a card that connects to the Aces, or connect to a card that connects to a card that connects to the Aces.)&amp;#10;7. A single hierarchy (a tree of cards connected to the the Aces) cannot contain both ascending sequences of cards and descending sequences of cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
